text:
When reviewing a franchise or a chain with more than one location I like to split my reviews into two parts. My titles are pretty self-explanatory. 

Specific to this location;
This Walmart is pretty average, very limited selection due to the neighborhood market store type but this place is fairly clean, and the service is pretty good. Can't really complain.

Wal-Mart in general;
Walmarts themselves vary from old or new, clean or dirty, and anything in between. Along with this comes variable service, selection, and the overall experience. Walmarts are known for being budget friendly and having a wide selection of common items that most people need on the fly. The stores themselves also offer different bonuses such pharmacies, auto centers, even other businesses inside of it such as salons, restaurants, and more.
